2.00	My_Favourite_Things_(album)	My Favorite Things (album)	My Favorite Things is the seventh album by jazz musician John Coltrane, released in 1961 on Atlantic Records, catalogue SD-1361. It was the first album to feature Coltrane's playing on soprano saxophone, and yielded a commercial breakthrough in the form of a hit single that gained popularity in 1961 on radio, an edited version of the title song, "My Favorite Things." In 1998, the album was a recipient of the Grammy Hall of Fame award.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/9/9b/My_Favorite_Things.jpg
